Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.76,0:00:38.48,中文,,0,0,0,,大卫·爱登堡：这是入口\N{\rEng}DAVID ATTENBOROUGH: This is the entrance
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.48,0:00:41.88,中文,,0,0,0,,到最伟大的自然奇观之一。\N{\rEng}to one of the greatest of natural wonders.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.64,0:01:02.64,中文,,0,0,0,,韩松洞，越南。\N{\rEng}Hang Son Doong, in Vietnam.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.24,0:01:12.96,中文,,0,0,0,,它被认为是地球上最大的洞穴。\N{\rEng}It's thought to be the largest cave on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.12,0:01:26.44,中文,,0,0,0,,在这里，地下200米处，\N{\rEng}Here, 200 metres underground,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.44,0:01:29.44,中文,,0,0,0,,一年中只有几周的时间，\N{\rEng}for just a few weeks a year,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.44,0:01:34.72,中文,,0,0,0,,阳光透过洞穴顶部的一个洞照射进来。\N{\rEng}sunbeams cast light through a hole in the cave's
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.16,0:01:54.32,中文,,0,0,0,,光线刚刚好\N{\rEng}There is just enough light
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.32,0:01:57.04,中文,,0,0,0,,使植物能够生长。\N{\rEng}to enable plants to grow.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.64,0:02:01.64,中文,,0,0,0,,但更深入的旅行，\N{\rEng}But travel deeper,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.64,0:02:03.84,中文,,0,0,0,,黑暗又回来了。\N{\rEng}and darkness returns.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.92,0:02:09.32,中文,,0,0,0,,而你达到了极限\N{\rEng}And you reach the limit
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.32,0:02:11.48,中文,,0,0,0,,生命可以存在的地方。\N{\rEng}of where life can exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.96,0:02:35.20,中文,,0,0,0,,我们星球上这些最极端的地方\N{\rEng}These most extreme places on our planet
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.20,0:02:39.04,中文,,0,0,0,,往往是我们难以接触到的。\N{\rEng}are often hard for us to reach.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.92,0:02:45.08,中文,,0,0,0,,事实上，这个洞穴是最近才发现的。\N{\rEng}Indeed, this cave was only recently discovered.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.16,0:02:52.44,中文,,0,0,0,,它包含了许多惊喜。\N{\rEng}And it contains many surprises.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.96,0:03:01.40,中文,,0,0,0,,洞穴珍珠\N{\rEng}Cave pearls.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.40,0:03:03.56,中文,,0,0,0,,曾经微小的沙粒，\N{\rEng}Once tiny sand grains,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.56,0:03:06.72,中文,,0,0,0,,现在球体有网球大小。\N{\rEng}now spheres the size of tennis balls.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.48,0:03:19.36,中文,,0,0,0,,还有巨大的石笋...\N{\rEng}And giant stalagmites...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.80,0:03:22.68,中文,,0,0,0,,..几个世纪以来形成\N{\rEng}..formed over centuries
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.68,0:03:26.00,中文,,0,0,0,,由数十亿个单独的水滴组成。\N{\rEng}by billions of individual drops of water.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.96,0:03:36.24,中文,,0,0,0,,地下河流已雕刻\N{\rEng}Underground rivers have carved
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.24,0:03:39.48,中文,,0,0,0,,这条穿过石灰岩的伟大通道\N{\rEng}this great passage through the limestone.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.88,0:03:58.52,中文,,0,0,0,,长超过五英里\N{\rEng}Over five miles long
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.52,0:04:00.88,中文,,0,0,0,,并且在某些地方足够宽\N{\rEng}and wide enough in places
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.88,0:04:03.40,中文,,0,0,0,,以容纳一架大型喷气式飞机。\N{\rEng}to accommodate a jumbo jet.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.36,0:04:17.32,中文,,0,0,0,,而它就在这里，\N{\rEng}And it is here,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.32,0:04:20.20,中文,,0,0,0,,在洞穴最远的房间里，\N{\rEng}in the cave's furthest chamber,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.20,0:04:22.60,中文,,0,0,0,,那生命是可以找到的。\N{\rEng}that life can be found.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.64,0:04:32.28,中文,,0,0,0,,半透明的洞穴鱼...\N{\rEng}Translucent cave fish...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.08,0:04:35.72,中文,,0,0,0,,..还有虾。\N{\rEng}..and shrimps.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.52,0:04:40.00,中文,,0,0,0,,与世隔绝千年，\N{\rEng}Isolated for millennia,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.00,0:04:44.68,中文,,0,0,0,,其食物只不过是上面丛林中的营养物质。\N{\rEng}feeding on little more than the nutrients from t
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.56,0:04:54.84,中文,,0,0,0,,鱼完全瞎了\N{\rEng}The fish are completely blind
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.84,0:04:58.80,中文,,0,0,0,,并仅通过触摸就能找到路。\N{\rEng}and find their way about by touch alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.48,0:05:10.52,中文,,0,0,0,,这些地下世界已经到了极限\N{\rEng}These underground worlds are at the very limit
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.52,0:05:12.48,中文,,0,0,0,,生命可以存在的地方。\N{\rEng}of where life can exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.32,0:05:23.52,中文,,0,0,0,,但在地面之上，\N{\rEng}But above ground,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.52,0:05:25.92,中文,,0,0,0,,我们星球上最极端的条件\N{\rEng}our planet's most extreme conditions
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.92,0:05:28.36,中文,,0,0,0,,发现于两极。\N{\rEng}are found at the poles.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.36,0:05:30.52,中文,,0,0,0,,风声\N{\rEng}WIND WHISTLES
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.68,0:05:35.72,中文,,0,0,0,,在北方的这里，\N{\rEng}Here in the north,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.72,0:05:39.92,中文,,0,0,0,,冬季气温可降至-50摄氏度。\N{\rEng}winter temperatures can drop to -50 degrees Cels
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.20,0:05:45.48,中文,,0,0,0,,一年中有四个月，\N{\rEng}For four months of the year,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.48,0:05:48.32,中文,,0,0,0,,几乎没有一丝阳光。\N{\rEng}there is barely a glimmer of sunlight.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.64,0:05:57.04,中文,,0,0,0,,但这里也一样，\N{\rEng}But here, too,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.04,0:05:59.08,中文,,0,0,0,,生命找到了生存之道。\N{\rEng}life finds a way to survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.60,0:06:06.88,中文,,0,0,0,,一群北极狼。\N{\rEng}A pack of Arctic wolves.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.40,0:06:15.36,中文,,0,0,0,,它们浓密的皮毛保护了它们\N{\rEng}Their dense fur has protected them
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.36,0:06:18.08,中文,,0,0,0,,经历数月的严寒。\N{\rEng}through months of bitter cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.44,0:06:28.20,中文,,0,0,0,,但现在太阳又回来了。\N{\rEng}But now the sun is returning.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.80,0:06:44.08,中文,,0,0,0,,这是埃尔斯米尔岛。\N{\rEng}This is Ellesmere Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.92,0:06:56.44,中文,,0,0,0,,短暂的夏季给了狼队重建实力的机会。\N{\rEng}The short summer gives the wolves a chance to re
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.44,0:07:12.08,中文,,0,0,0,,但在北极这里...\N{\rEng}But here in the Arctic...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.72,0:07:16.36,中文,,0,0,0,,..生活从来都不容易。\N{\rEng}..life is never easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.32,0:07:32.28,中文,,0,0,0,,这个群体由一位经验丰富的女性领导。\N{\rEng}This pack is led by an experienced female.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.76,0:07:43.52,中文,,0,0,0,,如果她不能带他们去吃东西\N{\rEng}If she can't lead them to food,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.52,0:07:46.96,中文,,0,0,0,,即将到来的冬天可能是他们的最后一个冬天。\N{\rEng}the coming winter could be their last.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.24,0:08:01.20,中文,,0,0,0,,猎物分布在如此广阔的区域\N{\rEng}Prey is spread over such a vast area
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.20,0:08:04.40,中文,,0,0,0,,他们必须不断地移动......\N{\rEng}that they must be constantly on the move...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.68,0:08:10.48,中文,,0,0,0,,..正在寻找它。\N{\rEng}..in search of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.60,0:08:28.16,中文,,0,0,0,,但寻找猎物仅仅是开始。\N{\rEng}But finding prey is only the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.44,0:08:40.00,中文,,0,0,0,,麝香牛。\N{\rEng}Musk oxen.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.00,0:08:43.52,中文,,0,0,0,,它们的体型是狼的五倍。\N{\rEng}They are five times the size of a wolf.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.64,0:09:01.48,中文,,0,0,0,,牛鼻息\N{\rEng}OXEN SNORT
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.56,0:09:10.72,中文,,0,0,0,,狼与牛的冲突由来已久，\N{\rEng}The conflict between wolf and oxen is an ancient
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.72,0:09:13.96,中文,,0,0,0,,自冰河时代以来就一直存在。\N{\rEng}and has been waged since the Ice Age.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.88,0:09:21.36,中文,,0,0,0,,牛咕噜声\N{\rEng}OXEN GRUNT
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.44,0:09:28.40,中文,,0,0,0,,双方都知道对方的战术。\N{\rEng}Each side knows the other's tactics.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.04,0:09:45.84,中文,,0,0,0,,狼群试图隔离\N{\rEng}The wolves try to isolate
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.84,0:09:48.20,中文,,0,0,0,,弱者或年轻人。\N{\rEng}the weak or the young.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.60,0:09:56.20,中文,,0,0,0,,一头牛犊绊倒了……\N{\rEng}A calf stumbles...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.20,0:09:59.88,中文,,0,0,0,,..狼群首领立即逼近。\N{\rEng}..and the pack leader immediately closes in.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.60,0:10:06.96,中文,,0,0,0,,狼叫声\N{\rEng}WOLF YELPS
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.48,0:10:14.00,中文,,0,0,0,,但牛群重新集结，\N{\rEng}But the herd regroups,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.00,0:10:16.16,中文,,0,0,0,,号角已准备就绪。\N{\rEng}horns at the ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.12,0:10:22.52,中文,,0,0,0,,牛咕噜声\N{\rEng}OXEN GRUNT
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.28,0:10:27.16,中文,,0,0,0,,僵局。\N{\rEng}Stalemate.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.72,0:10:31.60,中文,,0,0,0,,但它只能是简短的。\N{\rEng}But it can only be brief.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.76,0:10:59.68,中文,,0,0,0,,这一次，牛群竞相向更高的地方跑去。\N{\rEng}This time, the herd race to higher ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.52,0:11:15.40,中文,,0,0,0,,当他们到达山脊顶端时，\N{\rEng}As they reach the top of the ridge,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.40,0:11:18.32,中文,,0,0,0,,雄性则转身自卫。\N{\rEng}the males turn to defend themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.32,0:11:20.04,中文,,0,0,0,,牛吼声\N{\rEng}OXEN GROWL
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.64,0:11:23.96,中文,,0,0,0,,僵局...\N{\rEng}Stalemate...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.96,0:11:25.24,中文,,0,0,0,,..再次。\N{\rEng}..again.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.52,0:11:56.36,中文,,0,0,0,,每一次失败的狩猎\N{\rEng}Every unsuccessful hunt
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.36,0:11:59.16,中文,,0,0,0,,使狼群变得虚弱。\N{\rEng}leaves the pack weakened.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.24,0:12:17.32,中文,,0,0,0,,这可能是一顿更容易的饭菜。\N{\rEng}This could be an easier meal.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.80,0:12:21.36,中文,,0,0,0,,狼嗅\N{\rEng}WOLF SNIFFS
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.36,0:12:23.92,中文,,0,0,0,,但有些不对劲。\N{\rEng}But something is not right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.28,0:12:31.28,中文,,0,0,0,,这只麝牛死于疾病。\N{\rEng}This musk ox has died from a disease.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.28,0:12:33.00,中文,,0,0,0,,狼嗅嗅\N{\rEng}WOLVES SNIFF
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.00,0:12:36.92,中文,,0,0,0,,类似的疫情爆发变得越来越普遍\N{\rEng}Outbreaks like this are becoming increasingly co
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.92,0:12:40.16,中文,,0,0,0,,随着北极地区气候变暖。\N{\rEng}as the climate warms across the Arctic.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.64,0:12:48.88,中文,,0,0,0,,尽管他们很饥饿，\N{\rEng}Despite their hunger,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.88,0:12:51.76,中文,,0,0,0,,狼群不吃这具尸体。\N{\rEng}the pack don't eat this carcass.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.68,0:13:18.48,中文,,0,0,0,,又一群。\N{\rEng}Another herd.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.48,0:13:20.92,中文,,0,0,0,,包的另一个机会。\N{\rEng}Another chance for the pack.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.96,0:13:42.68,中文,,0,0,0,,这一次，狼群成功地分裂了狼群。\N{\rEng}This time, the wolves manage to split the herd.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.28,0:13:46.96,中文,,0,0,0,,这可能会增加他们的机会。\N{\rEng}That may improve their chances.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.84,0:14:07.84,中文,,0,0,0,,女领头确保牛\N{\rEng}The lead female makes sure that the oxen
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.84,0:14:10.36,中文,,0,0,0,,不要再次到达山脊。\N{\rEng}do not reach the ridge again.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.00,0:14:21.68,中文,,0,0,0,,少了一名后卫，小牛就更容易受到攻击。\N{\rEng}With one less defender, the calf is more vulnera
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.28,0:14:32.68,中文,,0,0,0,,牛犊叫声\N{\rEng}OXEN CALF CALLS
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.68,0:14:41.48,中文,,0,0,0,,非常需要的一顿饭。\N{\rEng}A much-needed meal.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.76,0:14:56.76,中文,,0,0,0,,狼队必须继续发挥最大作用\N{\rEng}The wolves must continue to make the most
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.76,0:14:59.44,中文,,0,0,0,,夏天剩下的几周……\N{\rEng}of the remaining weeks of summer...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.68,0:15:06.60,中文,,0,0,0,,..所以当冬天回来时\N{\rEng}..so when winter returns
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.60,0:15:09.52,中文,,0,0,0,,..他们已经准备好忍受\N{\rEng}..they're ready to endure
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.52,0:15:11.92,中文,,0,0,0,,一些最恶劣的条件\N{\rEng}some of the harshest conditions
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.92,0:15:15.40,中文,,0,0,0,,存在于地球上的。\N{\rEng}that exist on planet Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.32,0:15:40.60,中文,,0,0,0,,如此荒凉的极端\N{\rEng}Such inhospitable extremes
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.60,0:15:43.24,中文,,0,0,0,,不仅在两极发现。\N{\rEng}are not only found at the poles.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.00,0:15:52.88,中文,,0,0,0,,随着海拔的升高...\N{\rEng}As altitude increases...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.88,0:15:55.08,中文,,0,0,0,,..气温下降。\N{\rEng}..temperatures fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.00,0:16:06.16,中文,,0,0,0,,在这里，动物也必须充分利用季节变化。\N{\rEng}Here, too, animals must make the most of the sea
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.88,0:16:17.64,中文,,0,0,0,,特别是当你准备好交配时。\N{\rEng}Particularly if you're ready to mate.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.16,0:16:28.84,中文,,0,0,0,,一只雄性普通青蛙\N{\rEng}A male common frog
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.84,0:16:31.44,中文,,0,0,0,,在法国阿尔卑斯山。\N{\rEng}in the French Alps.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.88,0:16:43.36,中文,,0,0,0,,他整个冬天都在冰下冬眠。\N{\rEng}He has spent all winter hibernating under the ic
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.72,0:16:49.72,中文,,0,0,0,,但现在是时候醒来了。\N{\rEng}But now it's time to wake up.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.60,0:16:56.04,中文,,0,0,0,,他是冷血动物，需要阳光来温暖自己的身体。\N{\rEng}Being cold-blooded, he needs the sun to warm his
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.16,0:17:01.32,中文,,0,0,0,,但一旦几小时后开始\N{\rEng}But once it sets in a few hours' time,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.32,0:17:03.84,中文,,0,0,0,,他可能会被冻死。\N{\rEng}he could freeze to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.80,0:17:09.72,中文,,0,0,0,,所以找对象当务之急。\N{\rEng}So finding a mate is urgent.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.60,0:17:16.84,中文,,0,0,0,,天气好。\N{\rEng}The weather is good.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.44,0:17:23.28,中文,,0,0,0,,他开始滑雪橇。\N{\rEng}And he starts to sledge.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.12,0:17:30.32,中文,,0,0,0,,但这不是一场独青蛙竞赛。\N{\rEng}But this is not a one-frog race.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.76,0:17:35.04,中文,,0,0,0,,数十只正涌向繁殖池。\N{\rEng}Dozens are rushing to the breeding pool.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.80,0:17:42.96,中文,,0,0,0,,山坡上有这么多青蛙...\N{\rEng}This many frogs out on the slopes...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.96,0:17:45.16,中文,,0,0,0,,..不会被忽视。\N{\rEng}..doesn't go unnoticed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.04,0:17:51.36,中文,,0,0,0,,你买不起任何单据。\N{\rEng}You can't afford any slips.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.76,0:18:02.24,中文,,0,0,0,,一切都很顺利。\N{\rEng}It was all going so well.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.92,0:18:17.80,中文,,0,0,0,,做好了。\N{\rEng}Made it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.80,0:18:19.64,中文,,0,0,0,,青蛙呱呱叫\N{\rEng}FROG CROAKS
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.24,0:18:25.32,中文,,0,0,0,,但所有雌性都已经有了伴侣。\N{\rEng}But all the females have already got partners.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.36,0:18:31.44,中文,,0,0,0,,只有一件事可以做到这一点。\N{\rEng}There's only one thing for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.76,0:18:36.32,中文,,0,0,0,,摔角。\N{\rEng}Wrestling.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.72,0:18:54.60,中文,,0,0,0,,这次不行。\N{\rEng}Not this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.04,0:19:03.96,中文,,0,0,0,,Another latecomer.\N{\rEng}Another latecomer.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.48,0:19:07.36,中文,,0,0,0,,一名女性。\N{\rEng}A female.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.72,0:19:12.80,中文,,0,0,0,,她会是那个人吗？\N{\rEng}Could she be the one?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.96,0:19:26.72,中文,,0,0,0,,有时迟到也会有回报。\N{\rEng}Sometimes being late can pay off.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.40,0:19:55.00,中文,,0,0,0,,经过他的努力，雄性不会放过这个机会\N{\rEng}After all his efforts, the male is not going to
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.00,0:19:57.36,中文,,0,0,0,,从他的手指间溜走。\N{\rEng}slip through his fingers.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.68,0:20:21.96,中文,,0,0,0,,这是北非阿特拉斯山脉的雪松林。\N{\rEng}This is the cedar forest of the Atlas Mountains,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.88,0:20:32.24,中文,,0,0,0,,这些巴巴里猕猴度过了一个充实的夏天，\N{\rEng}These Barbary macaques enjoyed a summer of plent
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.24,0:20:34.24,中文,,0,0,0,,但现在他们正在付出代价。\N{\rEng}but now they're paying the price.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.48,0:20:42.12,中文,,0,0,0,,这里的冬天可能很残酷。\N{\rEng}Winter here can be brutal.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.28,0:20:51.72,中文,,0,0,0,,在某些年份，超过一半的群体死亡。\N{\rEng}In some years, over half the group perish.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.76,0:20:58.80,中文,,0,0,0,,但在这个猕猴社会里，\N{\rEng}But in this macaque society,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.80,0:21:02.04,中文,,0,0,0,,猴子越善于社交，\N{\rEng}the more social the monkey,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.04,0:21:04.88,中文,,0,0,0,,生存的可能性就越大。\N{\rEng}the more likely it is to survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.16,0:21:11.88,中文,,0,0,0,,通过挤在一起取暖可以使一切变得不同。\N{\rEng}Keeping warm by huddling can make all the differ
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.12,0:21:18.96,中文,,0,0,0,,但他们不能整天挤在一起。\N{\rEng}But they can't huddle all day.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.68,0:21:26.56,中文,,0,0,0,,最终，它们必须分开进食。\N{\rEng}They must, eventually, break apart to feed.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.00,0:21:41.60,中文,,0,0,0,,他们分散开来，寻找食物。\N{\rEng}They spread out, searching for food.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.20,0:22:06.12,中文,,0,0,0,,但每天晚上，这群人都会回到雪松树丛中。\N{\rEng}But each night, the group return to huddle in th
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.48,0:22:22.00,中文,,0,0,0,,没有人愿意被排除在外。\N{\rEng}No-one wants to be left out.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.12,0:22:27.00,中文,,0,0,0,,尤其是婴儿。\N{\rEng}Especially the infants.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.80,0:22:30.88,中文,,0,0,0,,猕猴吱吱声\N{\rEng}MACAQUE SQUEAKS
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.12,0:22:41.20,中文,,0,0,0,,这个婴儿不知何故已经分开了。\N{\rEng}This baby, somehow, has got separated.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.88,0:23:00.20,中文,,0,0,0,,他必须回到能救命的温暖的拥抱中，\N{\rEng}He must get back to the life-saving warmth of th
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.20,0:23:02.32,中文,,0,0,0,,等等。\N{\rEng}and soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.64,0:23:31.40,中文,,0,0,0,,但有一个障碍。\N{\rEng}But there is an obstacle.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.88,0:23:40.88,中文,,0,0,0,,脾气暴躁的雄性对婴儿的态度相当冷淡。\N{\rEng}A grumpy male is giving the baby a rather cold s
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.40,0:23:46.36,中文,,0,0,0,,成年猕猴的咕噜声\N{\rEng}ADULT MACAQUE GRUNTS
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.88,0:23:49.92,中文,,0,0,0,,婴儿猕猴的叫声\N{\rEng}INFANT MACAQUE CHITTERS
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.88,0:23:55.96,中文,,0,0,0,,也许是一种更微妙的方法。\N{\rEng}Maybe a more subtle approach.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.64,0:24:07.68,中文,,0,0,0,,男子决定离开。\N{\rEng}The male decides to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.64,0:24:25.16,中文,,0,0,0,,终于...\N{\rEng}At last...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.16,0:24:28.24,中文,,0,0,0,,..热情的接待。\N{\rEng}..an enthusiastic reception.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.44,0:24:40.20,中文,,0,0,0,,男性的运气则较差。\N{\rEng}The male has had less luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.44,0:24:44.32,中文,,0,0,0,,这可能是一个漫长的夜晚。\N{\rEng}It could be a long night.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.44,0:24:53.88,中文,,0,0,0,,拥抱似乎是一种简单的爱意表达，\N{\rEng}Huddling might seem a simple expression of affec
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.88,0:24:57.48,中文,,0,0,0,,但对于这些猕猴来说，它对于生存至关重要。\N{\rEng}but among these macaques it's essential for surv
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.16,0:25:03.36,中文,,0,0,0,,而且不仅仅是这里。\N{\rEng}And not just here.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.12,0:25:12.44,中文,,0,0,0,,5000英里外，在墨西哥的森林里，\N{\rEng}5,000 miles away, in the forests of Mexico,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.44,0:25:15.36,中文,,0,0,0,,帝王蝶，以百万计，\N{\rEng}monarch butterflies, in millions,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.36,0:25:18.72,中文,,0,0,0,,也为了生存而挤在一起。\N{\rEng}also huddle for survival.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.32,0:25:26.60,中文,,0,0,0,,他们都曾穿越北美\N{\rEng}All of them have travelled across North America
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.60,0:25:30.20,中文,,0,0,0,,为了躲避即将到来的冬天。\N{\rEng}to escape the winter that is coming there.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.12,0:25:36.92,中文,,0,0,0,,这片海拔3000米的森林，\N{\rEng}This forest, at an altitude of 3,000 metres,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.92,0:25:40.08,中文,,0,0,0,,似乎并不能提供多少安慰……\N{\rEng}might seem to offer little comfort...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.08,0:25:46.16,中文,,0,0,0,,..这里的气温可能会降至冰点以下，\N{\rEng}..for temperatures here can drop below freezing,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.16,0:25:49.68,中文,,0,0,0,,这可能会杀死蝴蝶。\N{\rEng}and that could kill the butterflies.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.56,0:25:57.76,中文,,0,0,0,,但事实上，有一层薄薄的暖空气\N{\rEng}But in fact, a thin layer of warm air
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.76,0:26:01.28,中文,,0,0,0,,被树冠困住可以保护他们，\N{\rEng}trapped by the tree canopy protects them,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.28,0:26:04.00,中文,,0,0,0,,并且整个冬天都会这样做......\N{\rEng}and will do so throughout the winter...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.76,0:26:10.16,中文,,0,0,0,,..前提是森林不受干扰。\N{\rEng}..provided that the forest remains undisturbed.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.36,0:26:19.44,中文,,0,0,0,,然而，不可预测的极端天气\N{\rEng}Unpredictable extremes of weather, however,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.44,0:26:23.20,中文,,0,0,0,,会破坏这种微妙的平衡。\N{\rEng}can disrupt this delicate balance.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.60,0:26:31.44,中文,,0,0,0,,强风会深入森林，使空气变冷。\N{\rEng}Strong winds can push deep into the forest, chil
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.80,0:26:35.76,中文,,0,0,0,,阵风\N{\rEng}WIND GUSTS
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.24,0:26:39.80,中文,,0,0,0,,数十万只蝴蝶\N{\rEng}Hundreds of thousands of butterflies
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.80,0:26:42.36,中文,,0,0,0,,可能会从树枝上被吹下来。\N{\rEng}may be blown from the branches.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.72,0:27:14.48,中文,,0,0,0,,在某些年份，暴风雨会杀死 75% 冬眠帝王蝶的生命。\N{\rEng}In some years, storms kill 75% of hibernating mo
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.00,0:27:33.40,中文,,0,0,0,,这个居然活下来了……\N{\rEng}This one has survived...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.40,0:27:36.52,中文,,0,0,0,,..但在地面上。\N{\rEng}..but on the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.80,0:27:42.52,中文,,0,0,0,,夜间霜冻是致命的。\N{\rEng}And night-time frosts are fatal.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.96,0:27:47.76,中文,,0,0,0,,它不能留在这里生活。\N{\rEng}It can't stay here and live.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.28,0:27:55.40,中文,,0,0,0,,天太冷了，不能坐飞机\N{\rEng}It is too cold to fly,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.40,0:27:58.88,中文,,0,0,0,,但它必须以某种方式回到树枝上。\N{\rEng}but it must get back into the tree branches some
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.92,0:28:04.44,中文,,0,0,0,,所以它开始爬升。\N{\rEng}So it starts to climb.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.04,0:28:18.00,中文,,0,0,0,,这相当于一个人爬上摩天大楼。\N{\rEng}It's the equivalent of a human climbing up a sky
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.04,0:28:52.20,中文,,0,0,0,,安全，终于。\N{\rEng}Safety, at last.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.56,0:29:00.64,中文,,0,0,0,,随着春天的到来，\N{\rEng}As spring returns,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.64,0:29:04.40,中文,,0,0,0,,君主们从漫长的沉睡中醒来。\N{\rEng}the monarchs wake from their long slumber.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.60,0:29:26.24,中文,,0,0,0,,现在地球上最伟大的自然奇观之一开始了。\N{\rEng}And now starts one of the Earth's greatest natur
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.24,0:30:02.24,中文,,0,0,0,,但这种大规模的觉醒正面临威胁。\N{\rEng}But this mass awakening is under threat.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.40,0:30:09.12,中文,,0,0,0,,气候变化正在创造更多的极端天气，\N{\rEng}The changing climate is creating more extreme we
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.12,0:30:12.20,中文,,0,0,0,,风暴变得越来越频繁。\N{\rEng}and storms are becoming more frequent.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.56,0:30:19.44,中文,,0,0,0,,但就目前而言，这一自然奇迹仍在继续。\N{\rEng}But, for now, this miracle of nature continues.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.48,0:30:30.92,中文,,0,0,0,,火。\N{\rEng}Fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.80,0:30:38.16,中文,,0,0,0,,不可预测且具有破坏性。\N{\rEng}Unpredictable and destructive.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.52,0:30:49.52,中文,,0,0,0,,这是南非的fynbos。\N{\rEng}This is South Africa's fynbos.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.52,0:30:53.20,中文,,0,0,0,,从植物学角度来说，它是地球上最多样化的栖息地之一......\N{\rEng}Botanically one of the most diverse habitats on
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.44,0:30:57.64,中文,,0,0,0,,..拥有超过 8,000 种不同的植物物种。\N{\rEng}..with over 8,000 different plant species.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.64,0:31:02.92,中文,,0,0,0,,然而，每二十年，\N{\rEng}Yet, every two decades,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.92,0:31:06.16,中文,,0,0,0,,火将植被烧成灰烬。\N{\rEng}fire reduces the vegetation to ashes.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.88,0:31:16.00,中文,,0,0,0,,这看起来可能是灾难性的。\N{\rEng}This may seem catastrophic.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.20,0:31:21.76,中文,,0,0,0,,但仅仅几天后，植物就焕发了生机……\N{\rEng}But just days later, plants burst into life...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.76,0:31:24.40,中文,,0,0,0,,..并改变景观。\N{\rEng}..and transform the landscape.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.20,0:31:32.60,中文,,0,0,0,,种子和球茎一直在等待这一事件。\N{\rEng}Seeds and bulbs have been waiting for this event
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.20,0:31:44.40,中文,,0,0,0,,与火一起经历了 9000 万年的进化\N{\rEng}90 million years of evolution alongside fire
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.40,0:31:47.88,中文,,0,0,0,,使一些植物如此紧密地适应\N{\rEng}has made some plants so closely adapted
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.88,0:31:52.12,中文,,0,0,0,,如果没有烟雾，它们就无法发芽。\N{\rEng}that they can't germinate without the presence o
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.36,0:32:04.92,中文,,0,0,0,,值得注意的是，地球上约 50% 的陆地栖息地\N{\rEng}Remarkably, around 50% of planet Earth's terrest
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.92,0:32:08.24,中文,,0,0,0,,依靠火来保持健康。\N{\rEng}depend on fire to remain healthy.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.08,0:32:19.76,中文,,0,0,0,,在澳大利亚北部，这些大草原需要季节性火灾\N{\rEng}In Northern Australia, these savannahs need seas
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.76,0:32:24.04,中文,,0,0,0,,保持它们开放并防止附近森林蔓延。\N{\rEng}to keep them open and prevent the spread of the
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.12,0:32:31.20,中文,,0,0,0,,它们是重要的栖息地\N{\rEng}And they are a vital habitat
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.20,0:32:33.88,中文,,0,0,0,,对于这位色彩缤纷的居民。\N{\rEng}for this colourful resident.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.52,0:32:43.20,中文,,0,0,0,,罕见的金肩鹦鹉。\N{\rEng}The rare golden-shouldered parrot.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.52,0:32:48.84,中文,,0,0,0,,他和他的终生伴侣..\N{\rEng}He and his lifelong partner..
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.84,0:32:53.64,中文,,0,0,0,,食物都依赖草原...\N{\rEng}rely on grassland for both food...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.64,0:32:56.00,中文,,0,0,0,,..和一个巢穴。\N{\rEng}..and a nest site.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.52,0:33:02.20,中文,,0,0,0,,像往常一样，它们把卵产在白蚁丘的洞里。\N{\rEng}As usual, they've laid their eggs in a hole in a
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.20,0:33:04.12,中文,,0,0,0,,叽叽喳喳\N{\rEng}CHIRPING
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.80,0:33:09.20,中文,,0,0,0,,现在有四只小鸡了。\N{\rEng}And now there are four chicks.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.80,0:33:16.40,中文,,0,0,0,,厚厚的泥墙不仅可以保护雏鸟免受捕食者的侵害，\N{\rEng}The thick mud walls don't only protect chicks fr
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.40,0:33:20.64,中文,,0,0,0,,但要使它们免受烈日的炎热。\N{\rEng}but insulate them from the heat of the scorching
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.16,0:33:30.32,中文,,0,0,0,,距离雏形仅剩几天，\N{\rEng}With fledging just days away,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.32,0:33:32.88,中文,,0,0,0,,父母都在加班。\N{\rEng}the parents are working overtime.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.68,0:33:39.32,中文,,0,0,0,,他们每天收集数千颗种子。\N{\rEng}They collect thousands of seeds every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.36,0:34:04.08,中文,,0,0,0,,但他们有一个问题。\N{\rEng}But they have a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.04,0:34:16.20,中文,,0,0,0,,火灾季节变得越来越不规律。\N{\rEng}The fire season is becoming more irregular.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.32,0:34:37.48,中文,,0,0,0,,如果他们还没有准备好起飞，\N{\rEng}If they are not ready to fly,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.48,0:34:40.40,中文,,0,0,0,,小鸡们无处可逃。\N{\rEng}chicks have no escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.24,0:35:08.96,中文,,0,0,0,,但选择在白蚁丘中筑巢有一个意想不到的好处。\N{\rEng}But choosing to nest in a termite mound has a su
