Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.76,0:36:33.40,中文,,0,0,0,,他们的世界现在已经存在了。\N{\rEng}that their world now exists at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.92,0:36:43.64,中文,,0,0,0,,人类正在影响地球上的栖息地。\N{\rEng}Humans are affecting habitats across planet Eart
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.64,0:36:46.04,中文,,0,0,0,,对于野生动物来说，很多时候，\N{\rEng}For wildlife, all too often,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.04,0:36:49.28,中文,,0,0,0,,后果是灾难性的。\N{\rEng}the consequences have been disastrous.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.48,0:36:55.76,中文,,0,0,0,,大象叫声\N{\rEng}ELEPHANT CALLS
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.96,0:37:01.88,中文,,0,0,0,,大象是最宽容的动物之一。\N{\rEng}Elephants are among the most tolerant of animals
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.88,0:37:04.84,中文,,0,0,0,,大象隆隆声\N{\rEng}ELEPHANT RUMBLES
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.84,0:37:07.48,中文,,0,0,0,,它们的寿命非常长，\N{\rEng}They are very long-lived,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.48,0:37:12.08,中文,,0,0,0,,代际传递的知识使他们能够\N{\rEng}and knowledge passed between generations enables
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.08,0:37:15.40,中文,,0,0,0,,及时寻找食物和很少使用的水源\N{\rEng}to find food and little-used sources of water in
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.40,0:37:18.04,中文,,0,0,0,,面临着巨大的环境压力。\N{\rEng}of great environmental stress.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.20,0:37:22.52,中文,,0,0,0,,但即使在大象中，\N{\rEng}But even among elephants,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.52,0:37:25.72,中文,,0,0,0,,生存策略现在开始失败。\N{\rEng}survival strategies are now beginning to fail.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.80,0:37:37.04,中文,,0,0,0,,在肯尼亚安博塞利，连年的极端天气，\N{\rEng}In Amboseli, Kenya, years of extreme weather,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.04,0:37:40.64,中文,,0,0,0,,再加上家牛的过度放牧，\N{\rEng}combined with overgrazing by domestic cattle,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.64,0:37:44.92,中文,,0,0,0,,正在把这些草原化为尘土。\N{\rEng}are turning these grasslands to dust.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.48,0:38:16.88,中文,,0,0,0,,这位老太太已经40多岁了……\N{\rEng}This matriarch is over 40 years old...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.88,0:38:18.84,中文,,0,0,0,,大象隆隆声\N{\rEng}ELEPHANT RUMBLES
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.84,0:38:20.72,中文,,0,0,0,,..她已经活了下来\N{\rEng}..and she's already survived
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.72,0:38:23.72,中文,,0,0,0,,东非一些最严重的干旱。\N{\rEng}some of East Africa's worst droughts.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.88,0:38:31.28,中文,,0,0,0,,但今年，粮食严重短缺……\N{\rEng}But this year, food is in extremely short supply
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.20,0:38:37.44,中文,,0,0,0,,..她的家人正在努力寻找足够的食物。\N{\rEng}..and her family are struggling to find enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.92,0:38:49.04,中文,,0,0,0,,她的小儿子营养不良，身体虚弱……\N{\rEng}Her youngest son is malnourished and weak...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.16,0:38:57.56,中文,,0,0,0,,..并且落后于他的母亲和兄弟。\N{\rEng}..and is lagging behind his mother and brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.40,0:39:11.16,中文,,0,0,0,,她带领他们来到一片她熟悉的金合欢树林。\N{\rEng}She leads them to a pocket of acacia forest that
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.36,0:39:20.64,中文,,0,0,0,,但折断的树枝和倒下的树木\N{\rEng}But broken branches and fallen trees
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.64,0:39:24.16,中文,,0,0,0,,表明其他大象已经到过这里。\N{\rEng}show that other elephants have already been here
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.00,0:39:31.76,中文,,0,0,0,,剩下的值得吃的已经所剩无几了。\N{\rEng}There is very little left worth eating.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.84,0:39:43.64,中文,,0,0,0,,没有食物，他的母亲就无法产生足够的牛奶。\N{\rEng}Without food, his mother cannot produce enough m
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.92,0:39:49.68,中文,,0,0,0,,她别无选择……\N{\rEng}She has no choice...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.72,0:39:55.28,中文,,0,0,0,,..但要留下她日渐衰弱的小腿......\N{\rEng}..but to leave her weakening calf...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.92,0:39:59.96,中文,,0,0,0,,..并尝试在其他地方寻找食物。\N{\rEng}..and try to find food elsewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.24,0:40:12.40,中文,,0,0,0,,于是，她带着大儿子出发了……\N{\rEng}So, she and her elder son head off...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.40,0:40:14.68,中文,,0,0,0,,..没有他。\N{\rEng}..without him.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.00,0:40:41.48,中文,,0,0,0,,他只能希望他们能回来。\N{\rEng}He can only hope for their return.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.36,0:41:09.08,中文,,0,0,0,,苍蝇嗡嗡声\N{\rEng}FLIES BUZZ
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.48,0:41:20.08,中文,,0,0,0,,但对于他来说，时间已经不多了。\N{\rEng}But for him, time has run out.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.16,0:41:58.48,中文,,0,0,0,,没有什么是他的母亲或任何人，\N{\rEng}There is nothing his mother, or anybody,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.48,0:42:01.28,中文,,0,0,0,,本来可以救他的。\N{\rEng}could have done to save him.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.28,0:42:04.44,中文,,0,0,0,,低沉的隆隆声\N{\rEng}LOW RUMBLING
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.88,0:42:16.04,中文,,0,0,0,,在她的大儿子还活着的情况下，\N{\rEng}With her elder son still alive,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.04,0:42:18.72,中文,,0,0,0,,她的家人还有希望。\N{\rEng}there is hope for her family.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.56,0:42:24.80,中文,,0,0,0,,但前提是他们能够快速适应。\N{\rEng}But only if they can adapt quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.16,0:42:38.80,中文,,0,0,0,,事实证明，一些家庭具有很强的适应力。\N{\rEng}Some families are proving to be resilient.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.84,0:42:47.64,中文,,0,0,0,,他们正在长途跋涉，远离安博塞利……\N{\rEng}They're travelling long distances, away from Amb
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.84,0:42:55.16,中文,,0,0,0,,..并寻找新的食物和水源。\N{\rEng}..and finding new sources of food and water.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.60,0:43:15.60,中文,,0,0,0,,尽管干旱...\N{\rEng}And despite the drought...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.44,0:43:22.44,中文,,0,0,0,,..小牛正在出生。\N{\rEng}..calves are being born.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.24,0:43:44.24,中文,,0,0,0,,但鉴于变化的步伐\N{\rEng}But given the pace of change
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.24,0:43:46.60,中文,,0,0,0,,以及他们面临的挑战......\N{\rEng}and the challenges they face...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.96,0:43:52.08,中文,,0,0,0,,..有多少非洲大象能够适应？\N{\rEng}..how many of Africa's elephants will be able to
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.12,0:43:56.56,中文,,0,0,0,,他们能做得足够快吗？\N{\rEng}And can they do so fast enough?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.96,0:44:13.20,中文,,0,0,0,,戈壁滩。\N{\rEng}The Gobi Desert.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.76,0:44:19.84,中文,,0,0,0,,一片沙地和雪地。\N{\rEng}A land of sand and snow.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.36,0:44:28.28,中文,,0,0,0,,至少一百万年来，这一直是\N{\rEng}For at least a million years, this has been
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.28,0:44:32.24,中文,,0,0,0,,地球上最极端的栖息地之一。\N{\rEng}one of the most extreme habitats on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.72,0:44:39.56,中文,,0,0,0,,然而沙滩上的脚印\N{\rEng}Yet, footprints in the sand
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.56,0:44:43.04,中文,,0,0,0,,揭示这里有生命。\N{\rEng}reveal that there is life here.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.56,0:44:51.48,中文,,0,0,0,,一只雪豹。\N{\rEng}A snow leopard.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.48,0:44:54.04,中文,,0,0,0,,很少见到...\N{\rEng}Seldom seen...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.36,0:45:00.48,中文,,0,0,0,,..尤其是在如此炎热、干旱的条件下。\N{\rEng}..especially in such hot, arid conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.56,0:45:08.84,中文,,0,0,0,,它们生活在海拔2000米的地方，\N{\rEng}They live up to 2,000 metres above sea level,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.84,0:45:12.88,中文,,0,0,0,,并巡逻广阔的领土。\N{\rEng}and patrol vast territories.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.32,0:45:44.28,中文,,0,0,0,,他们很少在一起。\N{\rEng}They are rarely seen together.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.12,0:45:53.52,中文,,0,0,0,,一个妈妈...\N{\rEng}A mother...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.72,0:45:59.08,中文,,0,0,0,,..和幼崽。\N{\rEng}..with cubs.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.28,0:46:04.12,中文,,0,0,0,,第一次在这里拍摄\N{\rEng}Filmed here for the first time
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.12,0:46:06.92,中文,,0,0,0,,在如此亲密的细节中。\N{\rEng}in such intimate detail.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.72,0:46:11.84,中文,,0,0,0,,豹子咆哮\N{\rEng}LEOPARDS SNARL
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.96,0:46:18.36,中文,,0,0,0,,他们让我们一睹他们的家庭生活......\N{\rEng}And they give us a glimpse of their family life.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.40,0:46:21.36,中文,,0,0,0,,..就这样。\N{\rEng}..such as it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.00,0:46:36.40,中文,,0,0,0,,水研磨\N{\rEng}WATER LAPPING
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.92,0:46:41.28,中文,,0,0,0,,雪豹幼崽和妈妈待在一起\N{\rEng}Snow leopard cubs stay with their mothers
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.28,0:46:45.16,中文,,0,0,0,,比几乎所有其他大型猫科动物都长。\N{\rEng}longer than those of almost any other big cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.96,0:46:54.96,中文,,0,0,0,,他们在一起已经两年多了……\N{\rEng}They remain together for over two years...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.84,0:47:02.64,中文,,0,0,0,,..当他们学习如何应对极端情况时。\N{\rEng}..as they learn how to master the extremes.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.04,0:47:14.44,中文,,0,0,0,,他们做得很好，因此能够蓬勃发展\N{\rEng}Which they do so well that they are able to thri
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.44,0:47:18.40,中文,,0,0,0,,在一些最热、最冷的地方...\N{\rEng}in some of the hottest, coldest...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.40,0:47:21.28,中文,,0,0,0,,..以及地球上最高的地方。\N{\rEng}..and highest places on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.60,0:47:36.48,中文,,0,0,0,,有些动物，经过数百万年，\N{\rEng}Some animals, over millions of years,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.48,0:47:40.64,中文,,0,0,0,,已经进化出在极端恶劣条件下生存的方法。\N{\rEng}have evolved ways of surviving extremely hostile
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.68,0:47:48.00,中文,,0,0,0,,但随着极端变得更加极端......\N{\rEng}But as the extremes become more extreme...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.00,0:47:52.20,中文,,0,0,0,,..进化正在被超越。\N{\rEng}..evolution is being outpaced.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.12,0:48:04.48,中文,,0,0,0,,这些非凡的地方仍然有人居住\N{\rEng}These extraordinary places are still inhabited
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.48,0:48:06.92,中文,,0,0,0,,由地球上一些最具复原力的人\N{\rEng}by some of Earth's most resilient
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.92,0:48:09.08,中文,,0,0,0,,和适应性强的物种。\N{\rEng}and adaptable species.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.28,0:48:14.60,中文,,0,0,0,,但在我们瞬息万变的世界中......\N{\rEng}But in our rapidly changing world...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.08,0:48:21.04,中文,,0,0,0,,..这是地球，你可能再也见不到它了。\N{\rEng}..this is planet Earth as you may never see it a
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.44,0:48:29.28,中文,,0,0,0,,豹吼声\N{\rEng}LEOPARD YOWLS
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.64,0:48:47.56,中文,,0,0,0,,大卫·阿滕伯勒：地球上最极端的地方\N{\rEng}DAVID ATTENBOROUGH: The most extreme parts of ou
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.56,0:48:50.20,中文,,0,0,0,,并不总能在您期望的地方找到。\N{\rEng}are not always found where you might expect.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.16,0:48:57.16,中文,,0,0,0,,隐藏在越南森林深处的一个当地人，\N{\rEng}Hidden deep in the forests of Vietnam, a local m
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.16,0:49:00.48,中文,,0,0,0,,何庆先生做出了非凡的发现。\N{\rEng}Mr Ho Khanh, made an extraordinary discovery.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.08,0:49:22.08,中文,,0,0,0,,他当时并不知道，\N{\rEng}He didn't know it at the time,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.08,0:49:26.48,中文,,0,0,0,,但他偶然发现了可以说是世界上最大的洞穴。\N{\rEng}but he had stumbled upon arguably the largest ca
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.72,0:49:42.52,中文,,0,0,0,,受到 Ho Khanh 先生的发现的启发，\N{\rEng}Inspired by Mr Ho Khanh's discovery,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.52,0:49:46.64,中文,,0,0,0,,《行星地球》团队开始拍摄韩松洞。\N{\rEng}the Planet Earth team set out to film Hang Son D
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.72,0:49:50.84,中文,,0,0,0,,但首先，他们必须到达那里。\N{\rEng}But first, they have to get there.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.24,0:49:54.52,中文,,0,0,0,,我们离开了河谷，\N{\rEng}We've left the river valley,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.52,0:49:56.96,中文,,0,0,0,,我们现在正在上山到入口处。\N{\rEng}and we're walking uphill now to the entrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.96,0:49:59.00,中文,,0,0,0,,这只是茂密的森林。\N{\rEng}It's just thick, thick forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.72,0:50:03.96,中文,,0,0,0,,经过两天的艰苦跋涉，\N{\rEng}After trekking for two gruelling days,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.96,0:50:06.80,中文,,0,0,0,,队伍终于到了。\N{\rEng}the team finally arrive.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.80,0:50:10.16,中文,,0,0,0,,下面是韩松洞的入口，\N{\rEng}Down here is the entrance to Hang Son Doong,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.16,0:50:13.72,中文,,0,0,0,,在这片巨大的丛林中这个小小的开口。\N{\rEng}this tiny opening in this massive jungle.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.72,0:50:16.68,中文,,0,0,0,,令人惊奇的是居然有人发现了这个地方。\N{\rEng}It's amazing that anyone ever found this place.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.76,0:50:22.52,中文,,0,0,0,,我们即将进入接下来的 18 天，\N{\rEng}We're about to go in for the next 18 days,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.52,0:50:25.12,中文,,0,0,0,,从这里开始灯就亮了。\N{\rEng}and it's lights on from here on out.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.80,0:50:30.28,中文,,0,0,0,,当地专家带领团队穿越黑暗。\N{\rEng}Local experts guide the team through the darknes
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.52,0:50:33.96,中文,,0,0,0,,好吧，我可以走了吗？\N{\rEng}是的是的。\N{\rEng}OK, I can go?  Yes, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.36,0:50:38.20,中文,,0,0,0,,沉重的呼吸\N{\rEng}HEAVY BREATHING
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.12,0:50:43.60,中文,,0,0,0,,紧张地咯咯笑\N{\rEng}NERVOUS CHUCKLING
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.60,0:50:45.16,中文,,0,0,0,,我很好。\N{\rEng}我可以。\N{\rEng}I'm good. I'm OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.16,0:50:46.84,中文,,0,0,0,,实在是太滑了。\N{\rEng}It's just really slippery.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.80,0:50:54.32,中文,,0,0,0,,复杂的绳索系统引导他们下降 90 米。\N{\rEng}A complex system of ropes leads them down a 90-m
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.92,0:50:57.88,中文,,0,0,0,,无线电喋喋不休\N{\rEng}RADIO CHATTER
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.52,0:51:01.08,中文,,0,0,0,,好的。\N{\rEng}OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.08,0:51:02.36,中文,,0,0,0,,谢谢。\N{\rEng}Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.28,0:51:09.08,中文,,0,0,0,,经过四个小时攀爬岩石......\N{\rEng}After four hours clambering over rocks...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.08,0:51:11.08,中文,,0,0,0,,铁锅\N{\rEng}PAN SIZZLING
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.08,0:51:14.00,中文,,0,0,0,,......他们终于到达了他们的营地。\N{\rEng}...they finally reach what will be their camp.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.76,0:51:25.96,中文,,0,0,0,,团队醒来，迎接新的一天——\N{\rEng}The team wake to a new day -
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.96,0:51:27.92,中文,,0,0,0,,但在黑暗中。\N{\rEng}but in darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.92,0:51:29.68,中文,,0,0,0,,卢克，你睡得怎么样？\N{\rEng}How did you sleep, Luke?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.68,0:51:31.76,中文,,0,0,0,,相当疲惫。\N{\rEng}Quite tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.76,0:51:34.08,中文,,0,0,0,,这些都是我身后的帐篷。\N{\rEng}These are all of the tents behind me.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.08,0:51:37.64,中文,,0,0,0,,你可以看到他们很漂亮...\N{\rEng}You can see they are pretty...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.64,0:51:39.08,中文,,0,0,0,,..非常舒适。\N{\rEng}..pretty snug.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.08,0:51:42.32,中文,,0,0,0,,这是我们每天吃早餐的地方\N{\rEng}This is where we have our breakfast every day,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.32,0:51:44.60,中文,,0,0,0,,由一些出色的厨师制作。\N{\rEng}made by some amazing cooks.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.04,0:51:48.20,中文,,0,0,0,,这是我们的充电站。\N{\rEng}This is our charging station.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.20,0:51:50.60,中文,,0,0,0,,相机设备的电池，我们的灯的电池，\N{\rEng}Batteries for camera equipment, batteries for ou
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.60,0:51:52.76,中文,,0,0,0,,我们的头灯，这非常重要。\N{\rEng}our head torches, which are so important.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.80,0:51:56.64,中文,,0,0,0,,这是我们的水站。\N{\rEng}This is our water station.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.64,0:51:59.88,中文,,0,0,0,,我们所拥有的一切都是有人带来的，\N{\rEng}Everything that we have got has been brought in
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.88,0:52:02.68,中文,,0,0,0,,所以你不能洗澡或洗澡。\N{\rEng}so you can't shower or wash.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.68,0:52:04.96,中文,,0,0,0,,而且不仅仅是水。\N{\rEng}And it's not just water.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.96,0:52:09.64,中文,,0,0,0,,成吨的设备必须搬进洞穴，\N{\rEng}Tonnes of equipment has had to be carried into t
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.64,0:52:11.96,中文,,0,0,0,,每一寸路。\N{\rEng}every inch of the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.12,0:52:18.52,中文,,0,0,0,,现在在地下深处，强大的灯光\N{\rEng}Now deep underground, the powerful lights
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.52,0:52:20.84,中文,,0,0,0,,揭示这个洞穴有多么巨大。\N{\rEng}reveal just how vast this cavern is.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.28,0:52:23.96,中文,,0,0,0,,这是惊人的。\N{\rEng}That is amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.96,0:52:25.40,中文,,0,0,0,,看那个。\N{\rEng}它是...\N{\rEng}Look at that. It's...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.40,0:52:27.20,中文,,0,0,0,,它超大！\N{\rEng}It's huge!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.64,0:52:31.92,中文,,0,0,0,,当你打开每一盏灯时，\N{\rEng}As you turn on each of the lights,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.92,0:52:34.76,中文,,0,0,0,,这个巨大房间的另一部分显露出来。\N{\rEng}another part of this enormous chamber is reveale
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.48,0:52:40.48,中文,,0,0,0,,这是魔法。\N{\rEng}绝对神奇。\N{\rEng}It's magic. Absolutely magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.68,0:52:46.80,中文,,0,0,0,,为了尝试捕捉真实的比例，\N{\rEng}To try and capture the true scale,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.80,0:52:50.68,中文,,0,0,0,,该团队尝试了一种以前从未尝试过的拍摄技术。\N{\rEng}the team attempt a filming technique never tried
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.92,0:52:55.24,中文,,0,0,0,,我们正在尝试与无人机一起跳舞，\N{\rEng}We're trying to do a little bit of a dance with
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.24,0:52:59.36,中文,,0,0,0,,我们的一架无人机略低于另一架，\N{\rEng}whereby we have one drone sort of slightly below
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.36,0:53:03.48,中文,,0,0,0,,一个在拍摄，另一个在洞穴中照明。\N{\rEng}one filming the other one lighting a feature in
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.48,0:53:05.80,中文,,0,0,0,,这是一个非常狭窄的空间。\N{\rEng}It's a really tight space.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.80,0:53:07.88,中文,,0,0,0,,你什么也看不见。\N{\rEng}You can't see anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.88,0:53:09.80,中文,,0,0,0,,可能会出什么问题？\N{\rEng}What could go wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.80,0:53:11.64,中文,,0,0,0,,无人机嗡嗡声\N{\rEng}DRONE BUZZES
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.52,0:53:15.32,中文,,0,0,0,,好吧，慢一点。\N{\rEng}OK, slow down a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.92,0:53:19.00,中文,,0,0,0,,这让大家都有些紧张。\N{\rEng}It's making everyone a little nervous.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.12,0:53:22.72,中文,,0,0,0,,是的，卢克，别再往上爬了。\N{\rEng}Yeah, don't go up any higher, Luke.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.08,0:53:27.40,中文,,0,0,0,,好吧，这个高度不错。\N{\rEng}OK, that's a nice height.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.00,0:53:34.28,中文,,0,0,0,,用一架无人机照明和一架无人机拍摄......\N{\rEng}With one drone lighting and one drone filming...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.08,0:53:41.16,中文,,0,0,0,,..它们揭示了一些世界上最大的石笋的奇迹。\N{\rEng}..they reveal the wonder of some of the world's
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.08,0:53:53.20,中文,,0,0,0,,日子一天天过去，团队逐渐适应\N{\rEng}As the days pass, the team settle into
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.20,0:53:56.44,中文,,0,0,0,,地下生活的日常生活。\N{\rEng}the everyday routine of life underground.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.64,0:54:01.88,中文,,0,0,0,,这就是脱离电网的缩影。\N{\rEng}This is the epitome of being off-grid.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.88,0:54:04.00,中文,,0,0,0,,我们称之为跷跷板厕所\N{\rEng}We call that one seesaw loo
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.00,0:54:06.52,中文,,0,0,0,,因为它有点像在岩石上\N{\rEng}because it's kind of on a rock,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.52,0:54:09.16,中文,,0,0,0,,每次你坐在上面并向后靠时，\N{\rEng}and every time you sit on it and lean back,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.16,0:54:13.08,中文,,0,0,0,,你害怕会有灾难发生。\N{\rEng}you're scared that there's going to be a disaste
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.72,0:54:18.16,中文,,0,0,0,,最奇怪的是没有联系\N{\rEng}The strangest thing is having no connection
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.16,0:54:20.24,中文,,0,0,0,,对外界的任何事情。\N{\rEng}to the outside world whatsoever.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.24,0:54:23.72,中文,,0,0,0,,时间被扭曲了。\N{\rEng}地下没有任何意义。\N{\rEng}Time is warped. Nothing makes sense underground.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.32,0:54:32.48,中文,,0,0,0,,在没有日光的情况下，团队昼夜不停地工作\N{\rEng}Without daylight to guide them, the team work ro
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.48,0:54:35.48,中文,,0,0,0,,捕捉洞穴最独特的特征。\N{\rEng}to capture the cave's most unique features.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.16,0:54:39.44,中文,,0,0,0,,最特别的是，\N{\rEng}Most special of all,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.44,0:54:43.08,中文,,0,0,0,,一年只发生几周的事件。\N{\rEng}an event which happens only a few weeks a year.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.80,0:54:48.24,中文,,0,0,0,,为了到达那里，他们必须导航\N{\rEng}To get there, they must navigate
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.24,0:54:50.92,中文,,0,0,0,,穿过巨石场和狭窄的挤压。\N{\rEng}through boulder fields and tight squeezes.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.12,0:54:53.56,中文,,0,0,0,,BLEEP\N{\rEng}BLEEP
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.40,0:55:03.04,中文,,0,0,0,,大约五十万年前，这里\N{\rEng}Here, around half a million years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.04,0:55:05.28,中文,,0,0,0,,洞顶塌陷，\N{\rEng}the cave roof collapsed,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.28,0:55:08.00,中文,,0,0,0,,打开一扇通向外面世界的窗户。\N{\rEng}opening a window to the outside world.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.40,0:55:15.28,中文,,0,0,0,,团队等待合适的条件。\N{\rEng}The team wait for just the right conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.64,0:55:19.24,中文,,0,0,0,,我们已经在这里坐了好几个小时了。\N{\rEng}We've been sat here for hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.24,0:55:21.80,中文,,0,0,0,,最后，就在墙的右侧，\N{\rEng}And finally, just on the right-hand side of the
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.80,0:55:24.32,中文,,0,0,0,,我们可以看到最初的曙光。\N{\rEng}we can see the first signs of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.24,0:55:30.60,中文,,0,0,0,,经过几周的黑暗\N{\rEng}After weeks of darkness
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.60,0:55:32.48,中文,,0,0,0,,地下200米...\N{\rEng}200 metres underground...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.80,0:55:35.64,中文,,0,0,0,,..他们看到阳光\N{\rEng}..they see sunlight
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.64,0:55:38.00,中文,,0,0,0,,照亮洞穴地面。\N{\rEng}illuminate the cave floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.04,0:55:47.88,中文,,0,0,0,,它照亮这个巨大洞穴的方式......\N{\rEng}The way it just lights up this massive cave...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.88,0:55:51.28,中文,,0,0,0,,..当我们尝试用大约四到五个灯来做到这一点时\N{\rEng}..when we've been trying to do it with about fou
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.28,0:55:54.72,中文,,0,0,0,,甚至几乎无法照亮最小的部分。\N{\rEng}and barely even lighting the smallest section.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.72,0:55:56.64,中文,,0,0,0,,当阳光照进来的时候，它只是...\N{\rEng}When the sun comes in, it just...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:56.64,0:55:58.04,中文,,0,0,0,,他泡芙\N{\rEng}HE PUFFS
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.32,0:56:02.36,中文,,0,0,0,,我想每个人都起鸡皮疙瘩了。\N{\rEng}I think everyone's got goose bumps.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.68,0:56:11.48,中文,,0,0,0,,我想我一生中从未如此欣赏过阳光。\N{\rEng}I don't think I've ever appreciated sun so much
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.08,0:56:15.12,中文,,0,0,0,,太不可思议了。\N{\rEng}It's incredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.84,0:56:20.88,中文,,0,0,0,,看看背光的瀑布。\N{\rEng}Look at the backlit waterfalls.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.88,0:56:23.52,中文,,0,0,0,,他们下来的速度真慢。\N{\rEng}They're so slow coming down.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.52,0:56:26.32,中文,,0,0,0,,这确实是我见过的最好的事情之一。\N{\rEng}It's literally one of the best things I've ever
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.84,0:56:33.76,中文,,0,0,0,,对于船员来说，阳光标志着深刻的结束\N{\rEng}For the crew, the sunbeam marks a profound end
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.76,0:56:36.08,中文,,0,0,0,,他们在山洞里的时光。\N{\rEng}to their time in the cave.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.36,0:56:41.64,中文,,0,0,0,,我们在外面！\N{\rEng}We're outside!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.64,0:56:44.64,中文,,0,0,0,,它是那么绿，那么亮。\N{\rEng}It's so green, it's so bright.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.64,0:56:48.60,中文,,0,0,0,,回到地面感觉就像我们所属的地方。\N{\rEng}Being back above ground feels like where we belo
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.56,0:56:53.88,中文,,0,0,0,,想象一下还有什么其他极端情况真是令人惊奇\N{\rEng}It's a wonder to imagine what other extremes
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.88,0:56:58.28,中文,,0,0,0,,仍然位于地球表面之下。\N{\rEng}still lie beneath the surface of planet Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.72,0:57:09.04,中文,,0,0,0,,下次...\N{\rEng}Next time...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.04,0:57:11.28,中文,,0,0,0,,..人类世界..\N{\rEng}..the human world...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.92,0:57:21.84,中文,,0,0,0,,..动物必须找到新的生存方式......\N{\rEng}..where animals must find new ways to survive...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.96,0:57:24.92,中文,,0,0,0,,..在我们中间。\N{\rEng}..amongst us.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:31.60,0:57:35.32,中文,,0,0,0,,栖息地探索者让动物及其栖息地栩栩如生。\N{\rEng}Habitat Explorer brings animals and their habita
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.32,0:57:38.64,中文,,0,0,0,,探索这个免费的互动，并制作折纸动物。\N{\rEng}Explore this free interactive, and make origami
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.64,0:57:42.52,中文,,0,0,0,,访问 bbc.co.uk/planetearth3\N{\rEng}Go to bbc.co.uk/planetearth3
Dialogue: 0,0:57:42.52,0:57:45.08,中文,,0,0,0,,并点击开放大学的链接。\N{\rEng}and follow the links to the Open University.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.08,0:57:48.56,中文,,0,0,0,,或者要订购免费印刷版，请访问网站\N{\rEng}Or to order a free printed version, visit the we
Dialogue: 0,0:57:48.56,0:57:51.04,中文,,0,0,0,,或拨打屏幕上的号码。\N{\rEng}or call the numbers on the screen.

